<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Aedeagal shaft straight, ventrally at base with very short, paired tooth-like process (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17C, D</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate with apex truncated (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17H</figureCitation>
). Pygofer lobe process right-angled mediad, elongate, with apices contiguous (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17G, J</figureCitation>
), apices variably serrate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17K, L</figureCitation>
). Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="male">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Measurements.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
n=7. Length from apex of crown to apex of tegmina 3.0-3.3 mm. Crown median length 0.4-0.5 mm. Crown length next to eye 0.3 mm. Pronotum length 0.4 mm. Head width across eyes 0.9-1.0 mm. Pronotum width 0.9 mm. Ocellus diameter 27.3-34.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
; interocular distance 44.3-57.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. Crown angle by trigonometry 92.7-96.8°.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="genitalia">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Anal tube.</emphasis>
Conical dorsally, rectangular laterally. Incised about three quarters into pygofer (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17G, J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="pygofer">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pygofer.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Viewed laterally longer than wide (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17G</figureCitation>
). Basal fold straight, angled about 45° (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="pygofer lobe">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pygofer lobe.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Apex broadly rounded, medioposterior margin with medial and apical membranous disc-shaped structure (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17G, J</figureCitation>
). Compressed process on medioposterior margin, sclerotized, straight, long, orientation mediad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17J-L</figureCitation>
). Process with apical and subapical ventral teeth; apices contiguous (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17K, L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="subgenital plate">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Subgenital plate.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Apex truncated (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17H</figureCitation>
). Macrosetae in 2-3 irregular rows. Length to width 1.6-1.8 times longer than basal width at confluence of plate and valve. Apex orientation dorsoposteriad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="valve">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Valve.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Posterior margins broadly rounded (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="aedeagus">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aedeagus.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Base of shaft ventrally with short paired acuminate process; length of process less than width of shaft. Shaft straight (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17B-D</figureCitation>
). Gonopore elongate, subapical dorsally to ventromedially (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17A, C</figureCitation>
). Shaft with striate microsculpture (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17A</figureCitation>
). Dorsal apodeme reduced, preatrium elongate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="connective">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Connective.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Ratio stem length: greatest width 0.9 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="style">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Style.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Apophysis apex narrowly rounded. Preapical lobe rounded; anterior lateral arm with sides convergent, apex acute; arm 0.4-0.6 times longer than distal part (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17F</figureCitation>
, lateral view Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17I</figureCitation>
, macrosetae dorsal).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="female">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Female.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Latin, short, adjective and noun in apposition, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">curtus</emphasis>
, for the short spine of the aedeagus, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">verpa</emphasis>
. Masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Driehoek farm, Dwarsrivier, Sederberge, Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Distribution models for Retevolatus gen. nov. and Flavorubivolatus gen. nov. and distribution maps of some associated plants A potential natural distribution in south western part of South Africa (Western and Northern Cape Province), R. flexiverpus sp. nov., red square, R. semicurviverpus sp. nov., green circle, R. subspiniverpus sp. nov., blue triangle B potential natural distribution in south western part of South Africa (Western Cape Province), Flavorubivolatus spp, F. glabriverpus sp. nov., green square, F. tensiverpus sp. nov., red circle, F. curtiverpus sp. nov., yellow triangle C Salvia lanceolata D Phylica oleifolia E Seriphium saxatilis F Myrovernix intricata G Selago pustulosa." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493743" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18B</figureCitation>
, yellow triangle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The reddish color (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Flavorubivolatus gen. nov. and Renosteria species habitus A-D F. curtiverpus sp. nov. Dorsal habitus view, males. A Clanwilliam, female, dorsal B Clanwilliam, female, dorsal C Dwarsrivier, male, dorsal D Dwarsrivier, male, dorsal E-I Renosteria species: E R. overbergia, male F R. hoekoensis, male G R. hantamensis, male, Kamieskroon H R. hantamensis, female, Nieuwoudtville I R. goudinica, male. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493736" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11B-D</figureCitation>
) is similar to the color of 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. tensiverpus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tensiverpus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">F. tensiverpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Flavorubivolatus gen. nov. and Renosteria species habitus A-D F. curtiverpus sp. nov. Dorsal habitus view, males. A Clanwilliam, female, dorsal B Clanwilliam, female, dorsal C Dwarsrivier, male, dorsal D Dwarsrivier, male, dorsal E-I Renosteria species: E R. overbergia, male F R. hoekoensis, male G R. hantamensis, male, Kamieskroon H R. hantamensis, female, Nieuwoudtville I R. goudinica, male. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493736" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11F-I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Flavorubivolatus glabriverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. ovipositor A valvula 1 and valvifer 1, Dwarsrivier B valvula 2 and valvifer 2, Dwarsrivier C valvula 3 and valvifer 2, Dwarsrivier D valvula 2, apex, Dwarsrivier E valvula 2, midsection, Dwarsrivier F valvula 3, apex, Dwarsrivier G valvula 2, Clanwilliam H valvula 2, Sederberge I valvifer 2, Dwarsrivier J valvifer 1, Clanwilliam K valvula 2, midsection, Sederberge. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-C, H); 0.05 mm (D-G, I-K)." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493737" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">12A</figureCitation>
) which distinguish these two species from 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. glabriverpus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="glabriverpus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">F. glabriverpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that is yellowish (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Flavorubivolatus gen. nov. Dorsal and lateral habitus view, males, females and nymphs. A-E F. glabriverpus sp. nov. Dorsal and lateral habitus view, males, females and nymphs A Piketberg, male, dorsal B Clanwilliam, female, dorsal C Driehoek, female, dorsal D Sederberge, female, dorsal E Driehoek, female, lateral E-I F. tensiverpus sp. nov. dorsal and lateral habitus view, males, females F Cedarberg, female, dorsal G Clanwilliam, male, dorsal H Clanwilliam, female, lateral I Doltuin, female, lateral. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-D, F-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493735" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">10A, E</figureCitation>
). Pygofer lobe processes variable in apical serration, i.e. length and number of teeth (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Flavorubivolatus curtiverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia A aedeagus, apex B aedeagus, dorsal C aedeagus, ventral D aedeagus, lateral E connective F style G genital capsule, lateral H subgenital plate, ventral I style, lateral J pygofer, dorsal K pygofer process, caudal, Sederberge L pygofer process, caudal, Dwarsrivier." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493742" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">17K, L</figureCitation>
). The truncated, blunt apex of the subgenital plate and the elongated, transverse pygofer lobe process can clearly be distinguished on whole specimens (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Flavorubivolatus gen. nov. and Renosteria species habitus A-D F. curtiverpus sp. nov. Dorsal habitus view, males. A Clanwilliam, female, dorsal B Clanwilliam, female, dorsal C Dwarsrivier, male, dorsal D Dwarsrivier, male, dorsal E-I Renosteria species: E R. overbergia, male F R. hoekoensis, male G R. hantamensis, male, Kamieskroon H R. hantamensis, female, Nieuwoudtville I R. goudinica, male. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493736" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11D</figureCitation>
), and that allow distinction between this species and 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. glabriverpus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="glabriverpus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">F. glabriverpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. tensiverpus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tensiverpus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">F. tensiverpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The single female listed in material examined, (image in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Flavorubivolatus gen. nov. Dorsal and lateral habitus view, males, females and nymphs. A-E F. glabriverpus sp. nov. Dorsal and lateral habitus view, males, females and nymphs A Piketberg, male, dorsal B Clanwilliam, female, dorsal C Driehoek, female, dorsal D Sederberge, female, dorsal E Driehoek, female, lateral E-I F. tensiverpus sp. nov. dorsal and lateral habitus view, males, females F Cedarberg, female, dorsal G Clanwilliam, male, dorsal H Clanwilliam, female, lateral I Doltuin, female, lateral. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-D, F-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493735" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">10B</figureCitation>
) is tentatively included here. This species consists of a short series of males with overlapping records in one or other of the two species above. Signs of parasites or feminized specimens were absent, with all genitalia considered invariable, functional and distinct from 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. glabriverpus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="glabriverpus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">F. glabriverpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. tensiverpus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="tensiverpus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">F. tensiverpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All males were dissected. Records of an associated plant, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hilliard" authorityYear="1999" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Selago" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selago pustulosa" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="pustulosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Selago pustulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Distribution models for Retevolatus gen. nov. and Flavorubivolatus gen. nov. and distribution maps of some associated plants A potential natural distribution in south western part of South Africa (Western and Northern Cape Province), R. flexiverpus sp. nov., red square, R. semicurviverpus sp. nov., green circle, R. subspiniverpus sp. nov., blue triangle B potential natural distribution in south western part of South Africa (Western Cape Province), Flavorubivolatus spp, F. glabriverpus sp. nov., green square, F. tensiverpus sp. nov., red circle, F. curtiverpus sp. nov., yellow triangle C Salvia lanceolata D Phylica oleifolia E Seriphium saxatilis F Myrovernix intricata G Selago pustulosa." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493743" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18G</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution models">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution models</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Distributions were modelled with the species from the most localities (i.e. 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. flexiverpus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="flexiverpus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">R. flexiverpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as well as most numerous species and all species merged, with the latter model for 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2021" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Retevolatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Retevolatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Retevolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Distribution models for Retevolatus gen. nov. and Flavorubivolatus gen. nov. and distribution maps of some associated plants A potential natural distribution in south western part of South Africa (Western and Northern Cape Province), R. flexiverpus sp. nov., red square, R. semicurviverpus sp. nov., green circle, R. subspiniverpus sp. nov., blue triangle B potential natural distribution in south western part of South Africa (Western Cape Province), Flavorubivolatus spp, F. glabriverpus sp. nov., green square, F. tensiverpus sp. nov., red circle, F. curtiverpus sp. nov., yellow triangle C Salvia lanceolata D Phylica oleifolia E Seriphium saxatilis F Myrovernix intricata G Selago pustulosa." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493743" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18A</figureCitation>
and for 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2021" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Flavorubivolatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flavorubivolatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Flavorubivolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Distribution models for Retevolatus gen. nov. and Flavorubivolatus gen. nov. and distribution maps of some associated plants A potential natural distribution in south western part of South Africa (Western and Northern Cape Province), R. flexiverpus sp. nov., red square, R. semicurviverpus sp. nov., green circle, R. subspiniverpus sp. nov., blue triangle B potential natural distribution in south western part of South Africa (Western Cape Province), Flavorubivolatus spp, F. glabriverpus sp. nov., green square, F. tensiverpus sp. nov., red circle, F. curtiverpus sp. nov., yellow triangle C Salvia lanceolata D Phylica oleifolia E Seriphium saxatilis F Myrovernix intricata G Selago pustulosa." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493743" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18B</figureCitation>
, the former with a wider potential distribution. The first four Worldclim bioclimatic variables with the highest contribution to these models differed slightly. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2021" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Retevolatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Retevolatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Retevolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they were bio19, 18, 8 and 15, and in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2021" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Flavorubivolatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flavorubivolatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Flavorubivolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bio8, 15, 18 and 19. Bio8 is mean temperature in wettest quarter (winter), bio15 is precipitation seasonality, bio18 is precipitation in warmest quarter (summer) and bio19 is precipitation in coldest quarter (winter). Despite the wide distribution of some of the associated plants (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Distribution models for Retevolatus gen. nov. and Flavorubivolatus gen. nov. and distribution maps of some associated plants A potential natural distribution in south western part of South Africa (Western and Northern Cape Province), R. flexiverpus sp. nov., red square, R. semicurviverpus sp. nov., green circle, R. subspiniverpus sp. nov., blue triangle B potential natural distribution in south western part of South Africa (Western Cape Province), Flavorubivolatus spp, F. glabriverpus sp. nov., green square, F. tensiverpus sp. nov., red circle, F. curtiverpus sp. nov., yellow triangle C Salvia lanceolata D Phylica oleifolia E Seriphium saxatilis F Myrovernix intricata G Selago pustulosa." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493743" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18C-G</figureCitation>
), the range of these leafhoppers appears restricted to a small area. Personal observation of species on plants resembling 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Seriphium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Seriphium saxatilis" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saxatilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Seriphium saxatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the northern parts of South Africa have not produced specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2021" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Flavorubivolatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flavorubivolatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Flavorubivolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Extensive work on the leafhoppers associated with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Dicerothamnus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dicerothamnus rhinocerotis" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhinocerotis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Dicerothamnus rhinocerotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Theron has not shown that 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller, 2021" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Flavorubivolatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Flavorubivolatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Flavorubivolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was associated with this plant.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
